    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.16-17_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ARMY AND NAVY CLUB
                        <lb/>
                    WASHINGTON</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 6, 1925.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I scarcely know how to express my thanks for your beautiful book. It is beautiful in typography, binding, illustrations, and of course, in matter and text. I am sure it will have some wonderful reviews. As yet I have only had time to read the pretty lines "To Alice", the Preface and the two chapters," The Village of Crazy Horse" and "The Death of Crazy Horse". Both are splendid.</p>
                
                <p>Long ago I ordered a copy
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.12.16-17_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">17</fw>
                    
                    through Brentano's, but it is a great treat to have one of the special 500, autographed, and with your very kind words added. I thank you with all my heart.</p>
                
                <p>When Macmillan is sending out circulars, let him send one to Dr. Howard Randthalen, Salem Female Academy, Winston-Salem, North Carolina. It is a horrid name, but it is a venerable and thriving school of the <unclear>Marariaux</unclear>, with about 500 southern girls. Ranthalen is the Principal.</p>
                
                <p>Again my thanks, dear Doctor Neihardt, and my warm congratulations</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most faithfully yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed><hi rend="underline">H.R. Lemly.</hi></signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
